        <sec id="SEC2-1-2-3">
          <title>Bimodality score system</title>
          <p>The bimodality score system prioritizes genes of which expression is bimodal. We measure the discrepancy between the high and low expression components of a given gene using two statistics. First, we compare the log-likelihood of the data (namely <italic toggle="yes">Q</italic> score) under the null hypothesis with a single Poisson distribution versus the alternative hypothesis with <inline-formula><tex-math id="M00031" notation="LaTeX">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
